1
00:02:07,828 --> 00:02:10,030
Why are we going to the library?

2
00:02:12,165 --> 00:02:14,368
Like Zhongze said,

3
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:17,204
if our family business in Taiwan
is that big,

4
00:02:17,838 --> 00:02:21,208
we can find something about my family

5
00:02:22,209 --> 00:02:24,544
by searching through
all the newspapers and magazines.

6
00:02:25,112 --> 00:02:26,380
Maybe,

7
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:28,882
this can make me remember something.

8
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,755
I know this isn't a smart idea, but...

9
00:02:35,222 --> 00:02:37,491
You know, I can't expose who I am,

10
00:02:37,557 --> 00:02:42,062
and I can't let my family know I'm looking
for them. It's a hard thing to do.

11
00:02:42,496 --> 00:02:43,430
Yes.

12
00:02:44,564 --> 00:02:47,000
I mean, you can't just grab someone,

13
00:02:47,067 --> 00:02:49,436
and then ask, "Do you know where
the Daoming family is?"

14
00:02:50,237 --> 00:02:51,271
Why not?

15
00:02:51,638 --> 00:02:52,572
The problem is...

16
00:02:53,073 --> 00:02:54,274
Young lady.

17
00:02:54,508 --> 00:02:56,877
Excuse me. Do you know where
the Daoming family is?

18
00:02:56,943 --> 00:02:58,545
-The Daoming family?
-Yes.

19
00:02:58,779 --> 00:03:00,047
Of course, I know.

20
00:03:01,148 --> 00:03:02,883
Who doesn't know the Daoming Family?

21
00:03:04,985 --> 00:03:06,086
What?

22
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,688
Where is the Daoming Family?

23
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:09,856
They own many corporations in Taiwan.

24
00:03:09,923 --> 00:03:13,293
So many. Like everywhere.

25
00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:15,796
-Yeah.
-Really?

26
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:17,030
So...

27
00:03:17,664 --> 00:03:19,666
So where is it? You didn't tell me.

28
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,835
Do you see that palace-like building?

29
00:03:21,902 --> 00:03:23,270
That's run by that family.

30
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:25,338
You're really weird.

31
00:03:29,476 --> 00:03:31,011
Seriously?

32
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,647
What a coincidence.

33
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:37,150
Then...

34
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:48,295
Shall we take a look?

35
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:50,997
No way.

36
00:03:58,839 --> 00:04:01,108
-The pillow in the room isn't soft enough.
-Yes, ma'am.

37
00:04:01,174 --> 00:04:03,610
-The fruit basket isn't fresh enough.
-Yes, ma'am.

38
00:04:03,677 --> 00:04:06,613
-The room delivery service is sub-par.
-Yes, ma'am.

39
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:09,182
-The menu needs an update.
-Yes, ma'am.

40
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:12,819
Useless people have no place
in the Daoming family.

41
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:14,921
We fire employees who deserve it.

42
00:04:14,988 --> 00:04:16,056
Yes, ma'am.

43
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:17,758
Of course.

44
00:04:18,158 --> 00:04:19,559
You are included.

45
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:20,827
Yes, ma'am.

46
00:04:20,894 --> 00:04:24,064
So remember the words I just said,
because I won't say them again.

47
00:04:24,965 --> 00:04:27,267
-Do you understand?
-Yes.

48
00:04:31,972 --> 00:04:32,939
Also,

49
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:36,143
that's not your dust storage.

50
00:04:37,043 --> 00:04:39,513
-Wipe it clean as soon as possible.
-Yes, ma'am.

51
00:05:12,345 --> 00:05:14,014
I don't know what I'm afraid of.

52
00:05:16,216 --> 00:05:18,518
My mother can't be meaner
than the landlady.

53
00:05:19,619 --> 00:05:21,755
Yet I don't know why my feet...

54
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:32,766
An abnormal stranger.

55
00:05:35,202 --> 00:05:37,771
That's okay if she's just any stranger.

56
00:05:39,239 --> 00:05:41,975
She's a stranger
that should be familiar to you.

57
00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:44,244
That's what you're afraid of.

58
00:05:51,985 --> 00:05:53,653
I'll see what I can dig up.

59
00:05:57,324 --> 00:06:00,193
Your mother is our only lead.

60
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,662
However, since you have a huge family,

61
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,898
your mother shouldn't be
your only family member.

62
00:06:05,365 --> 00:06:09,202
I believe there must be nice people
in your family.

63
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:55,215
<i>Your mother is really killing it.</i>

64
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:56,883
<i>She got tons of work every day.</i>

65
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:00,720
<i>No matter she's in her office or others',</i>

66
00:07:00,887 --> 00:07:03,356
<i>she is always doing business,</i>

67
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:05,725
<i>even when she is eating.</i>

68
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:07,594
<i>She won't eat the dishes she ordered.</i>

69
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,597
<i>When she's free from business and eating,</i>

70
00:07:10,664 --> 00:07:12,632
<i>her mouth still won't stop,</i>

71
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:14,267
<i>because she's scolding people.</i>

72
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:16,836
<i>Hey, the routine.</i>

73
00:07:16,903 --> 00:07:18,972
<i>My mother's routine is the point, okay?</i>

74
00:07:20,473 --> 00:07:22,742
<i>Speaking of her routine, we got a problem.</i>

75
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:26,212
<i>There are some places
that she visits every day,</i>

76
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:29,816
<i>like restaurants and offices.</i>

77
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,485
<i>Yet she doesn't have a fixed schedule.</i>

78
00:07:32,819 --> 00:07:36,489
<i>Sometimes she would go straight home,
change her clothes and head out again.</i>

79
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:38,425
<i>Then, what are we doing here?</i>

80
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,428
<i>Don't worry.</i>

81
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:42,929
<i>I've followed her for days,</i>

82
00:07:43,096 --> 00:07:47,167
<i>and I finally get an action window.</i>

83
00:07:58,745 --> 00:08:01,314
<i>This is her only fixed routine.</i>

84
00:08:01,381 --> 00:08:04,117
<i>The restaurant is her first stop
every day.</i>

85
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:07,253
<i>After 12 minutes, at 7:57 a.m.,</i>

86
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,189
<i>she arrives at the restaurant.</i>

87
00:08:09,255 --> 00:08:14,594
<i>Once she receives the message,
we have 12 minutes before she comes back.</i>

88
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:20,767
Sir.

89
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,770
-Young master.
-Get out of my way.

90
00:08:26,373 --> 00:08:29,275
Butler Liu, the young master comes back...

91
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:38,752
It's strange. How...

92
00:08:42,288 --> 00:08:43,923
Young master. It's indeed you!

93
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:45,392
You finally come back.

94
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,494
Okay, start timing.

95
00:08:48,028 --> 00:08:49,095
Start...

96
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:04,744
What's the matter?

97
00:09:04,811 --> 00:09:06,746
Hello, ma'am, I'm Butler Liu.

98
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:10,216
Yes. I'm reporting to you that
the young master is back.

99
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:11,951
He brought a girl with him.

100
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:14,120
She is not Shancai.

101
00:09:14,187 --> 00:09:16,423
She... looks like a foreigner.

102
00:09:17,457 --> 00:09:18,558
Listen.

103
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:20,727
Stop the young master no matter what.

104
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:23,329
Understood. I'll go find him right now.
Understood...

105
00:09:28,301 --> 00:09:30,103
Everyone, assemble!

106
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:32,605
The young master is back
but he's gone again!

107
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:36,309
Find the young master!

108
00:09:38,044 --> 00:09:40,480
Tell the driver to park the car
at the entrance. Quickly.

109
00:09:58,731 --> 00:10:00,733
There are more up there. Let's go.

110
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:02,869
Quick.

111
00:10:08,675 --> 00:10:12,178
